# GTM Growth OS 🚀

A portfolio-grade, end-to-end **GTM Operating System** for a scaling revenue organization.

This project is designed to show how annual planning connects to weekly operating discipline. It is not only a dashboard. It is a forward-looking operating model that ties together board targets, quota, capacity, territories, comp, demand generation, BDR outbound, forecast cadence, action tracking, process standards, and planning program management.

## Core operating chain

```text
Board / Finance ARR targets
        ↓
Quarterly gross-new ARR requirements
        ↓
Segment mix + ACV targets
        ↓
Pipeline coverage and stage requirements
        ↓
AE capacity, quota, ramp, and hiring model
        ↓
CFO/CRO quarterly headcount budget model
        ↓
Sales compensation design
        ↓
Account universe and territory optimization
        ↓
Marketing demand generation requirements
        ↓
BDR outbound pipeline requirements
        ↓
Monte Carlo scenario war room
        ↓
CCO operating rhythm + forecast cadence
        ↓
Action/risk tracker + planning control tower
        ↓
Executive narrative + Excel export pack
```

## Why this project is different

Most GTM dashboards explain what happened. GTM Growth OS asks whether the plan is executable **before** the quarter starts and whether the org has the weekly operating cadence to catch execution risk before it becomes a missed quarter.

It demonstrates:

- Strategic finance target-setting
- ARR bridge logic
- Gross churn and expansion dynamics
- ACV and segment-mix strategy
- Pipeline coverage math
- Reverse funnel conversion math
- AE capacity and quota modeling
- CFO/CRO headcount budget planning
- Productive vs. ramping vs. open headcount coverage
- Attainment distribution curves
- Time-to-productivity cohort analysis
- Sales ramp / productivity assumptions
- Compensation accelerators
- Territory balancing
- Marketing lead and budget requirements
- BDR outbound capacity
- Scenario risk and probability of hitting plan
- CCO weekly forecast operating rhythm
- Forecast-call pre-read and decision mechanics
- Pipeline hygiene and stage standards
- Cross-functional action and risk tracking
- Annual planning program-management control tower
- Claude-style operating artifacts for pre-reads, risk memos, and planning updates
- Exportable executive planning artifacts

## New in v2: Operating rhythm layer

The v2 upgrade turns the project from a planning model into a GTM operating system.

New tabs:

```text
10 CCO rhythm
11 Forecast console
12 Standards library
13 Action + risk
14 Planning tower
15 Claude assistant
```

### 10 CCO rhythm

Maps the weekly, monthly, quarterly, and annual operating cadence:

- CCO forecast call
- Pipeline generation review
- Monthly GTM operating review
- QBR / pipeline council
- Annual planning control tower

Each cadence includes owners, participants, input due dates, decision focus, output artifacts, and system paths.

### 11 Forecast console

A Monday-morning forecast review console showing:

- Forecast submission status by leader
- Pipeline coverage by segment
- Commit / best-case / upside forecast coverage
- Pipeline created this week
- Pipeline slipped this week
- Pull-in opportunity
- Stage regressions
- Close-date pushes
- Hygiene score
- Inspection risk
- Forecast-call asks and decision log

### 12 Standards library

Turns tribal knowledge into operating standards:

- Stage entry/exit criteria
- Forecast category definitions
- Pipeline hygiene scorecard
- Rules of engagement
- Close-date movement rules
- Forecast submission standards
- Quota deployment standards

### 13 Action + risk

Tracks commitments coming out of operating reviews:

- Source meeting
- Action item
- Owner
- Function
- Due date
- Priority
- Risk category
- Status
- Days open
- Escalation flag

### 14 Planning tower

Program-management backbone for annual planning:

- Finance plan
- Segment targets
- Capacity plan
- Territory design
- Quota deployment
- Comp design
- Marketing plan
- BDR plan
- Systems readiness
- Enablement rollout

Each workstream has a DRI, input requirement, dependency, due week, status, risk, and executive decision needed.

### 15 Claude assistant

Generates deterministic operating artifacts without an API key:

- CCO forecast call pre-read
- GTM operating risk memo
- Annual planning status update

If you later want to wire in the Anthropic API, the module is intentionally isolated in:

```text
src/gtm_growth_os/process_ai.py
```

## CFO/CRO capacity planning module

The CFO/CRO HC budget tab does annual-planning work that is usually trapped across several spreadsheets:

- Maps quarterly finance targets to buffered quota-capacity requirements.
- Separates productive, ramping, and open AE headcount by quarter and segment.
- Converts ramp cohorts into ramp-adjusted quota capacity.
- Shows quota coverage against plan by quarter.
- Creates P10 / P50 / P90 attainment distribution curves.
- Calculates time-to-80%-productivity by hiring cohort.
- Produces segment-level headcount budget recommendations for CFO/CRO planning.
- Exports the capacity budget, cohorts, productivity analysis, and attainment percentiles in the Excel pack.

