## What to say this project is

> GTM Growth OS is an end-to-end operating system for a scaling GTM organization. The first layer translates company ARR targets into segment targets, ACV, pipeline coverage, quota capacity, productive/ramping/open headcount, compensation, territories, demand generation, and BDR outbound requirements. The second layer connects that annual plan to weekly execution discipline: forecast calls, pipeline reviews, pre-read standards, action tracking, process definitions, annual planning workstreams, and Claude-style operating artifacts. It shows how I would turn scattered spreadsheets, Slack threads, and tribal knowledge into a single operating mechanism that Sales, Strategy, Finance, HR, Marketing, BDR, and Systems can all run from.

## Optional future extensions

```bash
uv add "gtm-growth-os[wow]"
```

Ideas:

- Use OR-Tools for territory optimization with hard constraints.
- Use NetworkX to model account hierarchies and buying committees.
- Add Anthropic API calls to the Claude assistant module.
- Add real CRM exports and replace the synthetic account universe.
- Add Salesforce-style opportunity snapshots and week-over-week forecast history.
- Add GitHub Actions to run smoke tests on every push.
